	Allow SRC_DIR='.' and multiple files in SRC_URI; implementing:
	Create top-level /origsrc dir, instead of ${S}-orig;
	apply_patch tests different -p? args to determine correct patch level;
	Other transparent changes to accomodate.

	* Makefile.am (dist-hook):
	chmod 644 INSTALL.

	* bin/cygport.in:
	Formatting improvements.

	* bin/cygport.in (cygtest):
	Assure presence of Makefile, else error.

	* bin/cygport.in (__show_help, __show_version):
	List download and almostall commands in --help.
	Improve conformance with GNU Coding standards and help2man formatting.

	* bin/cygport.in (cygconf):
	Support running ${S}/configure in subdirs of ${B}; useful if running
	multiple configure's from the same tarball (e.g. fxscintilla, fftw3, 
	wxWidgets).
	Implement CYGCONF_SOURCE, to be set to the directory containing 
	configure, for those cases that it's not ${S}.

	* bin/cygport.in (unpack):
	Support RAR archives with unrar.
	Support non-tar .bz2 and .gz archives.
	Support .c, .patch, and .sh files.
	Ignore .md5 and .sig files.
	Support multiple arguments.

	* bin/cygport.in (pkg_diff):
	Ignore texinfo.tex and ylwrap.

	* test/bootstrap
	* test/messages:
	SKIP tests if called by 'cygport check'.

	* bin/cygport.in (apply_patch):
	Pass -t (--batch) to patch, and remove -Z (--set-utc).

	* bin/cygport.in (src_fetch)
	* lib/Makefile.am (cygclass_DATA)
